04/18/2024,"748.1335 - Admission, Service Planning, Discharge","Admission, Service Planning, Discharge",No,04/26/2024,06/17/2024,"I:Admission, Service Planning, Discharge",Medium Low,Yes,"During the inspection, it was found that one child file reviewed did not have a service plan and the child has been at the facility since 2/28/24.","On 6/17/24, the Administrator reported moving forward the operation will ensure the 45-day initial service plans are completed for children who they know will not be discharging from the operation within 45 days. The Administrator reported they will ensure to have this immediately available to licensing upon request.

Licensing discussed the expectation and requirement for this standard with the Milieu Coordinator, Administrator, and the Quality Management Coordinator.

On 6/20/24, this rep informed the operation by email (Quality Management Coordinator & Administrator) that they had not provided a follow up response to this citation and to provide one. This rep requested they email a 45-day initial service plan template be provided to licensing.

On 6/21/24, the operation Quality Management Coordinator provided a copy of a child's Biopsychosocial Assessment and four clinical treatment plans for this same child. The operation reported all documents were done within the state timeframe of 45 days. 

On 6/26/24, this rep sent the operation an email informing them the documents they provided do not suffice for what licensing considers an initial 45-day service plan. This rep referred them to review standard 748.1337 (link to CCR minimum standards was provided). This rep informed them that the initial 45-day service plan should be one document that has everything listed in standard 748.1337. This rep requested they provide a template once they have that. This rep informed them that the Biopsychosocial and the Suicide Assessment cannot be counted as the 45-day initial service plan as these are considered part of the Admission Assessment & Preliminary Service Plan (72-hr. plan). This rep informed them that the 45-day initial service plan should be a separate document."
