dietician for evaluation and consultation. The treatment team will review the results of the
registered dieticians recommendation and determine if the child needs to be seen by a medical provider for further consultation/evaluation. The Treatment Team meeting may be held without all team members present; however, each staff will be provided any opportunity to provide feedback for the meeting. The plan of action will be developed on an individual basis, based on the needs of the specific child, and may consist of - continued observation of meals or may go directly to sending the child to a Higher Level of Care (HLOC). If a child goes for more than 48 hours without nutritional consumption the child will be sent to a medical doctor for evaluation or possibly directly to a HLOC."
