On 8/18/21, a staff tested positive for a communicable disease. This incident was not reported to the A/N hotline.

On 9/7/21, a teenager hit the wall inside the operation and fell to the floor crying and hitting their head to the ground, then verbalized being upset, ""too tired"", and just want to ""kill"" themselves, then got up and went and grabbed a butterknife from the kitchen. This incident was not reported to the A/N hotline.

On 9/15/21, inappropriate sexual behaviors between two children in care were not reported to the A/N hotline.","Regarding the incident on 8/18/21, the oper. stated they will report any positive test for communicable disease(s) in the future within 24 hours of receipt of the test result. Regarding the incident on 9/7/21, the oper. reported that Program leadership discussed this incident and felt it did not meet the State Definition of a Suicide Attempt; therefore, did not require the oper. to make a report. In this case, the child was assessed as moderate risk and was being monitored in the following ways: staff
support to process and regulate; supervision was within line of sight upon regulation and child had reassessment in the morning and processing with therapist/PD. Regarding the incident on 9/15/21, the oper. reported that Program leadership discussed this incident and reviewed the standards and made the determination that it did not require reporting given that the children were of the same age and the behaviors were reported to be consensual, and there was no difference in their developmental or more than 24 months difference in biological age level. Both children's parents were notified of the event and the children were
immediately assigned to different rooms."
09/21/2021,748.1583(a) - Child Care,Child Care,No,10/19/2021,10/13/2021,J:Child Care,Medium,No,"During the inspection, it was found that a TB Exam was not available in the child file reviewed.","The oper. reported that Program administration will request this information during admission of each child. If this is unavailable at that time, the facility will obtain the documentation of
TB within two weeks of admission. For children with no current negative TB result, the facility will take them to an outside provider to obtain a TB test no later than the end of week 2 after admission."
