07/03/2021,748.685(c)(5) - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,09/01/2021,08/20/2021,Individual Standards Evaluated,Medium High,Yes,"It was found that a therapist had communicated the child's suicidal plan with other staff through Microsoft Teams, but had not included the nurse on shift administering the child's medications on the day of the incident (7/2/21). The therapist was aware of the child's suicidal plan to take pills during med pass and run away and get hit by a car as of 6/30/21. It was reported that the therapist communicated this with the morning shift nurse, however this may have not been relayed to the nurse on the next shift. It was reported that the child had expressed suicidal ideation on the day of the incident as well (7/2/21). It was reported that an email regarding the child's suicidal ideation was also sent to other staff on 6/27/21 although the email was not found.","All caregivers responsible for the children in care will use the Electronic Health Record (KIPU) for alert communication. All caregivers have access to KIPU. KIPU has an Alert System (Urgent Issues) to notify staff when there is any concerning situation and it requires the staff to acknowledge they have read the notification. The Program Director will ensure all staff are trained again by 9/1/2021 on the use of this system to ensure proper communication of any
concerning situations regarding resident safety at the facility."
07/03/2021,748.2003(b)(6) - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,09/01/2021,08/20/2021,Individual Standards Evaluated,Medium High,Yes,It was found that a nurse was administering medication to children in care during a time when this person was on a provisional status and had a condition to not administer medications. This was corrected by the operation.,"The Program Director and Milieu Manager will ensure that all staff will have completed State Background Checks. Furthermore, the Milieu Manager (Supervisor of Nursing Staff) will ensure that all Nursing staff will have State Backgrounds Clearance prior to administer any medication at the facility. The Milieu Manager can track and monitor the State Background Clearance status via the State Website. The State of Texas notifies the program if a staff members status has changed via U.S. Postal Service. If a staff member status is changed, the Program Director will ensure the operation follows any new provisional or conditional restriction outline until they can be resolved or permanently implemented into the staff job requirements (example  staff member my be restricted from driving the residents, but still able to complete other job requirements)."
07/03/2021,745.635(3) - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,08/21/2021,08/20/2021,Individual Standards Evaluated,High,Yes,"During the course of this investigation, it was discovered on 8/9/21, that the nurse involved in this incident was administering medications to the child involved and this nurse had been administering medications all along while on a provisional status for background check and had a condition to never be allowed to administer medication to children in the care of the operation, except for in a medical emergency to prevent the death or serious bodily injury of a child.

The operation was informed of this immediately and this was corrected by the operation. This person's background check was updated on 8/9/21 and although there are still other conditions for this person, the condition regarding not administering medications was removed.","The Program Director and Milieu Manager
will ensure that all staff will have completed State Background Checks. The Program
Director and the Milieu Manager will monitor the State Background Checks via the State
Website daily when a new staff has been hired. Furthermore, the Program Director will
ensure that any provisional or conditional status from the State Background Checks will
be followed and staff with provisional or conditional status will have written documentation outline what job duties they can perform until the provisional or
conditional status is resolved."
