01/07/2021,748.685(a)(4) - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,03/30/2021,03/30/2021,Individual Standards Evaluated,High,Yes,"After reviewing the investigation, it was found that on multiple occasions a child in care inappropriately touched two other children in care in a sexual manner without their permission and staff person(s) who were in charge of supervising all three children were not aware of the inappropriate touching taking place.","The operation reported all staff have been or are in the process of being retrained on Standard 748.685(a)(4) relating to Caregiver Responsibility  providing the level of supervision necessary to ensure each childs safety and well-being."" The operation reported the importance of continuous line of sight supervision for the safety and well-being of the children has specifically been emphasized and this additional training will be completed for all employees responsible for the supervision of children in care by 3/30/2021. Training is documented for each employee in the employees training file upon completion. 

