10/20/2020,748.399(a) - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,11/03/2020,11/03/2020,Individual Standards Evaluated,Medium,No,"During the inspection, the operation was unable to produce certain records to licensing upon request (i.e. pre-service and annual training record for staff file reviewed).","All staff have been retrained on the importance and urgency of uploading all training to their employee file in a timely manner. Additionally, leadership has been retrained by Human Resources on how to access employee trainings in personnel records through the HR electronic portal. Upon request, facility leadership can access a transcript of training for employees, as well as reach out via ""Zoom"" to the company HR department to show licensing requested documentation in personnel files.

A.) Should multiple representatives require computer access; the facility will be sure to provide the necessary work station. Furthermore, HR will provide multiple representatives to assist in navigation of employee records via ""Zoom"" video conferencing. 

B.) Currently the operation is in email correspondence with HHS to facilitate the annual health inspection. HHS informed the operation via automated recording that they are currently working remotely, and that email correspondence is the avenue in which to facilitate communication. 

The operation reported pertaining to ""Zoom"" conferences, the process would be as follows:
1.) Request is made to review records.
2.) The facility would contact the HR team, who would then send a Zoom link. Should multiple representatives require access at the same time, the facility will accommodate appropriately. The HR representative would stay on the video call with you and your team to provide real time assistance, and walk-throughs of requested information. 

The operation contacted Hays Country Development Services regarding setting up a health inspection instead of HHS. A copy of payment for the operation's annual health inspection was provided paid to Hays County Development Services. As of 11/10/20, the operation reported Hays County D. S. will be contacting them to schedule their health inspection. On 11/11, the operation reported that they have scheduled their health inspection for 11/13/20 and will send the results as soon as it is completed. On 11/13/20, the operation emailed their completed health inspection to licensing. There were no concerns noted on the inspection."
